# Vendored from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/backward/backward.n3
# Unmodified rule content. Previously blocked on having no goal-directed
# query mechanism at all (pure forward-chaining materialize() can never
# bind `?X math:greaterThan ?Y` with no facts to iterate candidates over).
# Now closed via `TripleStore::prove`/`BackwardChainer::prove`
# (lib/src/backwardchaining.rs): the concrete goal EYE's own
# `backward-query.n3` companion file seeds (`5 :moreInterestingThan 3`) is
# supplied by this suite's manifest entry's `prove_goal` field instead of
# being embedded in this fixture, since this crate's manifest-driven runner
# has no separate "query file" concept -- the goal is proved directly
# against this document's rules via goal-directed backward chaining, with
# real builtin dispatch (math:greaterThan) reused from the ordinary
# forward-chaining query engine.
@prefix math: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/math#>.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#>.
@prefix : <http://example.org/#>.

{
    ?X :moreInterestingThan ?Y.
} <= {
    ?X math:greaterThan ?Y.
}.
